  <data name="AboutArch.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Architectural Features:</value>
  </data>
  <data name="AboutArch1.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>• Modifications are isolated in RAM and do not damage the original file until saved.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="AboutArch2.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>• Thread-safe asynchronous search processed in 64 KB blocks.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="AboutDesc.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>High-speed professional hex editor designed for instantly opening files of any size (from a few bytes to hundreds of gigabytes). The application utilizes data stream and UI virtualization, saving RAM and maintaining maximum FPS during scrolling.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="AboutDev.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Developer: AI Collaboration &amp; C# WinUI Community</value>
  </data>
  <data name="AboutDialog.CloseButtonText" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Got it</value>
  </data>
  <data name="AboutDialog.Title" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Documentation &amp; User Guide</value>
  </data>
  <data name="AboutTitle.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Fast WinUI 3 HEX Editor</value>
  </data>
  <data name="AboutVersion.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Version: 1.0.0 (Stable Release)</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect1.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>1. WORKING WITH FILES AND TABS</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect1_1.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>• Opening:</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect1_2.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Via 'File -&gt; Open file...' menu you can select any document. Each new file opens isolated in its own tab.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect1_3.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>• Closing:</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect1_4.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Click the tab's close button. The file handle memory (FileStream) will be instantly released to the OS.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect2.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>2. MULTIPLE BYTE SELECTION</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect2_1.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>• Single Choice:</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect2_2.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Clicking LMB (Left Mouse Button) on a cell selects the byte. Its address is duplicated in the bottom status bar.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect2_3.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>• Range Selection (Drag &amp; Drop):</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect2_4.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Hold LMB on the starting byte and drag the cursor through the table up or down. The grid will highlight the chosen array. The right mouse button is locked to prevent selection reset.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect3.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>3. BYTE-BY-BYTE EDITING</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect3_1.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>• Enter Editing Mode:</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect3_2.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Double-click (Double Tap) a byte to bring the cell into input focus.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect3_3.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>• Character Typing Process:</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect3_4.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Type HEX characters [0-9] or [A-F]. Pressing the first key shifts the byte into a semi-input state (e.g., 'A?'). The second press writes the byte permanently, updates its ASCII character on the right, colors the text RED, and automatically moves the cursor to the next step.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect3_5.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>• Cancel and Navigation:</value>
  </data>
  <data name="ManualSect3_6.Text" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Pressing the Escape key resets the cell editing mode. You can navigate between cells during input using the arrow keys.</value>
  </data>
